<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="United Kingdom">
  <data key="d0">United Kingdom</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">The United Kingdom is a European country and a NATO member state that has experienced significant geopolitical and domestic shifts. Following Brexit, the nation saw a change in migrant numbers. In its foreign policy, the United Kingdom is actively seeking to join the SAFE defense fund and strengthen its ties with the European Union. It maintains a security relationship with the United States, though this relationship has faced tension due to disagreements over the war with Iran. The UK has also been described as a former great ally of the United States. In military operations, the United Kingdom operates RC-135W intelligence aircraft and has planned to send a military vessel to defend Cyprus, though this plan faced delays due to labor union restrictions. Furthermore, American B-1B Lancer bombers are reported to be operating from the UK to conduct strikes against Iran. Domestically, families and businesses in the United Kingdom experience fluctuating energy bills, which have been attributed in part to the actions of foreign leaders.&lt;SEP&gt;The United Kingdom is a country that is part of the E3 format.&lt;SEP&gt;United Kingdom is a Western state accused of preventing the signing of the Istanbul Agreement.</data>
