<node id="Europe">
  <data key="d0">Europe</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Europe is a continent and multifaceted political entity encompassing European Union member states, the United Kingdom, and other European countries. Geographically, it serves as a defining region from which non-European countries are contrasted in discussions of migration trends. As a political actor, Europe is described as needing stronger security and defense cooperation, with capabilities to counter a potential invasion—including one involving Russian-terrorist forces—through the use of air power and precision weapons. Within this context, Russian propagandists are noted as seeking to “break” the political will of Europe, while some perspectives portray Europe as having lost its sovereignty and being weak.

Simultaneously, Europe is characterized as a region facing serious economic and energy crises. The continent is also the subject of ongoing discussions about internal unity and disagreements, highlighting the complexities of its political cohesion. These varied descriptions reflect Europe both as a cohesive geopolitical bloc and as a collection of nations with distinct challenges and divergent viewpoints on security, sovereignty, and crisis management.&lt;SEP&gt;Europe is the region where political plans of Trumpists and Putinists were disrupted by leaks.&lt;SEP&gt;Europe is referenced as a location that does not need defense from Ukraine, according to Viktor Orbán.&lt;SEP&gt;Europe is a continent that the source text says should learn from South Korea's response to territorial violations.&lt;SEP&gt;Europe is a continent mentioned in the context of achieving peace with Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;Europe is the region where the process of neo-Nazi and jihadist convergence was slower compared to the United States.&lt;SEP&gt;Europe is a region that opposes Donald Trump's ambition to establish control over Greenland.</data>
