<node id="European Union">
  <data key="d0">European Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Union (EU) is a political and economic union of European member states, functioning as an intergovernmental bloc and often described as a rare island of stability in the contemporary global context. It serves as the overarching organization to which bodies like the Council of the European Union (Foreign Affairs) belong. The EU is a principal actor in managing sanctions and aid to Ukraine, which is considered for membership in the union. Financially, the EU has allocated €90 billion to Ukraine under its budget guarantees, approved a loan to the country, and considered a 90 billion euro war loan. The bloc has proposed multiple sanctions packages against Russia, including an 18th and a proposed 20th package targeting Russian banks, and has also proposed sanctions against the entity 2Rivers. The EU is considering a decision to use Russian assets for a reparations loan for Ukraine, and its ambassadors agreed on a 90 billion euro sanctions package, though Slovakia threatened to block the 20th package. The EU granted an exception to Hungary and Slovakia regarding the import of Russian oil in 2022. New data from the EU indicates that Ukraine has a financial buffer until the end of April, and the EU also finances the repair of the Ukrainian section of the Druzhba pipeline and provides technical support.

The EU has experienced significant internal conflict, particularly with Hungary. Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán has accused Brussels of dictating policy and opposing support for Ukraine, blocking a 90 billion euro credit and paralyzing key EU reforms, though he supported a proposed EU fact-finding mission to Ukraine. In response, the EU has excluded Hungary from official events, blocked confidential information exchange, and proposed stripping Budapest of its veto power regarding Ukraine’s accession. The EU froze approximately 18 billion euros in funds for Hungary due to a lack of reforms. The bloc has faced allegations that Hungarian Foreign Minister Péter Szijjártó passed information from closed EU meetings to Russian officials; EU intelligence services have possessed transcripts and data on specific issues since 2016-2017 and are aware of a Moscow secret mission in Hungary. Internal documents have been leaked from the EU, which has also been the target of a hybrid war by Russia aimed at undermining its institutions. The EU is an organization whose important decisions Viktor Orbán helps block on behalf of Moscow, and its internal discussions were accessed by Russia through the Orbán government. Additionally, secret documents were allegedly leaked by the AfD. The EU is an organization targeted in a campaign of demonization, and is sometimes referred to as "Brussels" in petition text, criticized for prioritizing Ukraine. Overall, the EU is described as experiencing both euphoria and internal struggle, with ongoing discussions about unity and internal disagreements.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Union is a political and economic union of European countries, the rearmament of which is opposed by Greta Thunberg and her allies.&lt;SEP&gt;European Union is a political entity whose elites are described as having understood Russia's intentions and are tasked with strengthening Ukraine's defense.</data>
