<node id="Donald Trump">
  <data key="d0">Donald Trump</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Donald Trump is a former U.S. president and prominent political figure whose influence extends across international relations, European security, and domestic politics. He has significantly impacted European security dynamics through unpredictable behavior, including threats concerning Greenland and NATO. Trump has been criticized by UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer for negatively affecting energy bills for UK families and businesses through his actions abroad, and he escalated tensions with Starmer over the use of British military bases and criticized the UK’s offer to send aircraft carriers.

Trump has described as benefiting Russia and being a “dream” for Russian President Vladimir Putin, with both Putin and Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban praising him. Trump has expressed strong support for Orban, participating in a phone call alongside JD Vance and Gyorgy “GG” Divan during a rally in Hungary, where he voiced admiration for both the country and its leader. He urged the Hungarian people to vote for Orban, and preparations were underway for a potential meeting between Trump and Putin, possibly in Budapest. Trump’s administration is noted for offering economic support to Hungary, while he has been characterized as an agent for Russia and a threat to the EU. Allegations have been made that his real estate was used by the Russian mafia to launder millions of dollars. Trump was advised on when to call by Steve Witkoff, and he has been associated with a conservative "hamburger" concept. His image is used by Orban to validate his position and create the illusion that Orban is a visionary leading Europe to a new order.

In geopolitical contexts, Trump is a figure referenced in peace negotiations who should not be angered, and his typical excuse was referenced by a commenter in relation to Orban's rhetoric. As a former U.S. president, his visit to Hungary was expected by Viktor Orban but did not happen due to the war in Iran. Additionally, Trump’s July 2024 assassination attempt inspired Operation Gamechanger. In matters of energy policy, he stated that he has no objections to Russian oil deliveries to Cuba despite the energy blockade. Overall, Trump’s consistent support for Viktor Orban, his controversial impact on international alliances, and the various geopolitical and legal controversies surrounding him remain central themes.&lt;SEP&gt;Donald Trump is a person who signed an executive order on January 30 regarding tariffs.&lt;SEP&gt;Donald Trump is a political figure and former President of the United States whom Democrats tried to restrict from taking military action against Cuba.&lt;SEP&gt;Donald Trump is a political figure who expressed a desire to establish control over Greenland and is involved in geopolitical strategies.&lt;SEP&gt;Donald Trump is a US leader whom critics now remain silent about, according to Alice Weidel, despite violating the sovereignty of Venezuela and Greenland.&lt;SEP&gt;Donald Trump is the former president of the United States who applied military force to overthrow the leader of Venezuela, threatened the annexation of Greenland, and is perceived as helping his friends in Europe gain election ratings.</data>
