<node id="United States">
  <data key="d0">United States</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">The United States is a country and major global actor whose role in international affairs is characterized by multiple, often conflicting descriptions. It is portrayed as a transatlantic partner, though its reliability is considered shifting and less dependable, particularly concerning Europe and Russia. Tensions with the United Kingdom have been noted, especially under the leadership of President Donald Trump, during whose tenure the United States was characterized as not appearing to be a reliable ally. Its potential actions in a European conflict are described as uncertain, and it is a country with which Russia could potentially conflict. Conversely, the United States is also described as a global leader whose joint action is considered critical for preventing Russian expansion in Europe. It has been involved in a war against Iran, which Robert Fico describes as meaningless, and is described as a former collaborator with the EU and the British Empire, now under the control of marginal figures.

In diplomatic and political engagements, the United States has strong relations with Hungary, providing significant international support to Viktor Orbán. It sent its Vice President, J.D. Vance, to Budapest to support Orbán and develop the bilateral partnership. The United States was also proposed by Orbán to host a peace summit with Russia in Budapest, and its representatives, such as Secretary of State Marco Rubio, were in communication with Hungarian officials. CPAC, a major conservative political conference, is based in the country. The United States also began negotiations with the President of Cuba, imposed an energy blockade on Cuba, included Cuba on a list of countries prohibited from buying Russian oil, and sent a State Department delegation to Havana for secret negotiations. It is also a country with which the EU pursued free trade agreements, a policy opposed by the far-right in their October 2025 motion.

Regarding security and intelligence, according to JD Vance, elections in the United States were reportedly targeted by elements of Ukrainian special services. In 2024, the United States sanctioned the Social Design Agency for the Doppelganger operation. Through the CIA, it shared intelligence with Europe about Russian operations, and its Defense Intelligence Agency and CIA provided analysis regarding North Korean military supplies. The United States has begun to roll back sanctions on Russian oil. Alexander Dugin suggested the United States could use listed sovereign states as a military bridgehead. Additionally, the United States is the country where neo-Nazis were actively developing concepts like "White Sharia" and praising ISIS and Hamas during the pandemic, and where white far-right groups are setting the trend for the current "white jihad." It is also the country where Semen Mogilevich expanded his operations in the early 1980s and where the Russian mafia laundered money through real estate. The United States is the country of origin of Rob Schneider.&lt;SEP&gt;United States is a country whose Republicans Маркус Фронмайер has been actively establishing contacts with.&lt;SEP&gt;United States is a country whose role is discussed in the context of not being naive regarding Russia's intentions.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States is a country that conducted a successful operation in Venezuela and defines the Western Hemisphere as its sphere of influence.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States is the country whose former president, Donald Trump, used military force to overthrow the leader of Venezuela and threatened the annexation of Greenland.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-adcce0ecbb12090a19fa597edabfada4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4528714a664b747f0d79d200f4e5d6ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8dc136c80cd91ef2cf9ad9756a4d52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba68be1ab3264024852e59eb0966356d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a89cef022ba72f7cec7e5ae7c29101&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-efac8eca24c7251212c13175865647fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a55a1b2f7d86f155201f7562a7195495&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81536517f133c3a5924be660cac3eb05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-effd94d17758c91a975ace308b74d363&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8be82194b3f8b4851149bcd5709c9f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-84d9d2605d4824a81c0829b9eb92d7b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69d93e1cd4546542fd7a6dd43a3e688d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3da3b046ca1fff9119eaf735e34f56d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1561937403235278917e112e7843f5b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204b60f8b5f56bb209e8ca6cc9af48f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c3129b97ce4bf590efeb8acc86b772e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1704b3bc09f596547c35a95941e29e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d18298cbbd6dafd4125556d537885355&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17e8350a36758c6e44f8b72ee0cd6731&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ccdb895c49cc5a1b4f5807c901e88cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4219648b35dcbd430c607633467c92dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad59dda33fb37c7a475f7200ea184cf8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeeb3e654a660cb7b38dfc9d61222bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec746b6d0ff03701a4a50f1703d6bbdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3dc55aad4eb94544269bbfd9dec2905&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bea54a7e2da99c4d21fe120e09b5930&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d31f0e0677eda8305196001171ef666&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9ebb3ed519c434b35de7bc7a410af22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1a126d8b8691b4020263f5c90fd4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77d298742baea18cfade0750d3d81239&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a73e41ce47973ce6d0501f8f7acc0955&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bdde8f24aa613c9ae76329db019d6d7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c0e45973e2056f2a0c6c6cf9df17553&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c748c9a23ba05cffbc5245984ffc52e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-965b8760e7f023cb5fe999d79e061c32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64bdf9c0794ec3590