<node id="Kremlin">
  <data key="d0">Kremlin</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Kremlin is the central government authority and seat of political leadership of Russia, functioning as the official residence of the Russian President and the core decision-making body for the nation. It oversees military operations, nuclear threats, foreign policy, and strategic actions both domestically and internationally. The Kremlin is believed to orchestrate propaganda campaigns and has a noted disinformation apparatus, linked to entities such as the Social Design Agency. It has a long-standing alliance with Iran and is the government body whose intelligence dossiers have been shared by the CIA. Domestically, the Kremlin has been publicly opposed by protesters under slogans such as “Russians go home!” and is also reported to allow North Korean drugs on the Russian market as a form of gratitude for North Korea’s assistance in the war against Ukraine.

In its foreign relations, particularly with Central and Eastern Europe, the Kremlin views Viktor Orban as a key ally and has made efforts to keep him in power. It signed a deal with Orban in 2014 to expand the Paks II nuclear plant, is reported to have sent political technologists to Hungary, and is alleged to have compromised Semen Mogilevich’s tax problems in exchange for compromising videos of Orban. The Kremlin is believed to give orders to Orban and direct other political figures such as Robert Fico and Szijjarto. It is the government that Robert Fico is unsure can protect his elections after failures in Hungary, and the center he has attempted to visit. The Kremlin is also ideologically aligned with Orban and Fico, and its political technologists are associated with spoiler candidate tactics in post-Soviet countries. Furthermore, the Kremlin is the source of oil deliveries to Cuba and has been involved in decisions regarding pipeline strikes and sanctions, with advisors of French President Emmanuel Macron having contacted it regarding negotiations for peace between Russia and Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin is an entity that supports any political forces, even opposing ones, that are willing to destabilize Europe from within, operating without regard to ideology.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin is the government of Russia, which seeks to downplay the severity of the war's impact on the country.</data>
