<node id="Vladimir Putin">
  <data key="d0">Vladimir Putin</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Vladimir Putin is the President of Russia, widely regarded as the country’s authoritarian leader. His regime is characterized by its involvement in the war against Ukraine, where he has been described as having incorrectly assessed the strength of his own forces and has been referenced as a “bloody dictator.” His potential for further military action, including the possibility of invading Europe, has been a subject of discussion. Putin is also considered a global power figure described as an enemy of EU rules and stability, who has found certain representatives in Europe that began fighting against unity within the continent. He is an ally of Robert Fico and maintains significant international relationships, most notably with Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban. Orban considers Putin a friend and an ideological model, a friendship reportedly spanning 16 years, strengthened by economic deals such as one involving a nuclear power plant and a “friendly discount” on oil for Hungary. Putin has participated in phone conversations with Orban, praising Hungary’s position on the war against Ukraine and receiving promises of help; at one point, Putin reportedly laughed at a reference made during their discussion. These conversations have been leaked, and in one such call, Putin is referred to as the head of the Kremlin. Other Hungarian officials, such as Peter Szijjarto, have also met with Putin in Moscow. Additionally, the interests of Vladimir Putin are allegedly served by the actions of former U.S. President Donald Trump, and the Hungarian government’s alleged subservience to Putin has been noted. Putin has a strong interest in Viktor Orbán winning the election.

Putin is also the Russian leader who received a letter from Viktor Orban and responded that Russia’s reaction would be strong, taking into account the positions of individual countries. He ordered a group of political technologists and military intelligence to interfere in the Hungarian parliamentary elections. Furthermore, Putin provides support to North Korea in exchange for North Korean soldiers and pursued strategic rapprochement with Kim Jong Un, signing a mutual military assistance treaty. In the context of peace negotiations, he is a person who should not be angered.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Putin is a person referred to as a friend in the context of the source text, implied to be exempted from the tariff measures.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Putin is a person whom those calling for diplomacy are accused of sympathizing with.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Putin is the Russian leader who openly states his intentions and plans, including military goals in Ukraine and a strategy to influence European politics by supporting populist movements.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Putin is a leader accused by critics of violating international law, as mentioned in the statement.</data>
