<node id="Poland">
  <data key="d0">Poland</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Poland is a country that has allocated funds for the "Eastern Shield" project, which involves building fortifications along its border with Russia and Belarus. It is a neighboring country mentioned in contexts related to assembling or organizing military forces and is actively attempting to build its military strength. Poland's fighter jets currently protect Slovakia's airspace, and the country is connected to Lithuania via the Suwalki Gap, a strategically significant corridor. Politically, Poland is the home country of Donald Tusk, a prominent politician who serves as the country's prime minister. As prime minister, Tusk has made statements regarding various proposals and has addressed the Orbán-Putin leak. Additionally, Poland is a participant in the E4 format, a grouping of European nations.&lt;SEP&gt;Poland is an EU member state that is against Ukraine's accelerated EU accession.&lt;SEP&gt;Poland is a country whose airspace Robert Fico's office requested access to after being denied by Baltic states.&lt;SEP&gt;Poland is a country whose foreign minister, Radosław Sikorski, commented on Hungary's position.&lt;SEP&gt;Poland is a country mentioned in the text for its gasoline prices, as it has no dependence on Russian oil.&lt;SEP&gt;Poland is the country of origin of Mateusz Morawiecki.</data>
