  <data key="d0">Georgia</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Georgia is a country where the Russian army faced long-standing systemic communication problems.&lt;SEP&gt;A country where the Russian army also faced communication problems in the past, as referenced in the text.&lt;SEP&gt;Georgia is a country cited as a modern example of Russian aggression, alongside Crimea and Donbas.&lt;SEP&gt;Georgia is a country described as following the same path as Belarus toward Russian influence.&lt;SEP&gt;Georgia is a country where the spoiler candidate technology, associated with Kremlin political technologists, became entrenched.&lt;SEP&gt;Georgia is a country where Zoltan Andre worked under diplomatic cover from 2016 to 2020.&lt;SEP&gt;Georgia is a country whose sovereignty Alexander Dugin stated is unacceptable.</data>
