<node id="Moscow">
  <data key="d0">Moscow</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Moscow is the capital city of Russia and serves as the central hub for the country’s political decision-making, government operations, and international diplomacy. As the seat of Russian power, Moscow is frequently referenced in global geopolitical contexts, including being the location where Hungarian officials, such as Foreign Minister Péter Szijjártó, have met with Russian President Vladimir Putin. The city also hosts the Hungarian embassy, which has been described as a point of transmission for official documents. Moscow has been noted as a party seeking closer relations with Budapest, and its political future has been said to be influenced by the outcome of Hungarian elections. Additionally, Moscow has been associated with allegations of being the destination for leaked information from European Union meetings.

The city has appeared in published correspondence between Budapest and Moscow, suggesting Russian influence operations. Moscow has also been involved in coordination with Washington on a peace plan and was the intended destination of travel by Robert Fico. It is reported that Moscow secretly sent a team to Budapest for an operation referred to as "Operation Budapest." Furthermore, political technologists from Moscow are associated with the introduction of spoiler candidate tactics. The government of Russia, represented by Moscow, reportedly plans to conduct an information campaign to support Viktor Orbán, and the city was the destination of phone calls reportedly made by Péter Szijjártó to share details from EU meetings.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is the capital city of Russia and is referred to as a cooperating party with Pyongyang.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is a location that received artillery pieces from Pyongyang.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is the capital of Russia and is referred to as the recipient of North Korean support in the conflict.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is the location of the Gnessin Musical Academy.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is a geopolitical player that is impacted by the potential loss of power by Viktor Orban.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6610955fc2b94d091c65e9f7449d2028&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1d17587159dea209c75a0ae5875a4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9360bf859acb934b8ebad024d1c18290&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d35dd378774e42749ede8cf940deb5eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2843e721f5be37e2778dd3123cdcec43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35ef5418fbb73e10428a076cc8117782&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-313fbd5b1968d3d281c042524d458b06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec746b6d0ff03701a4a50f1703d6bbdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3311af1794addd390d80bf21ccd47d8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00452022e84a0076582b1330b967245d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba1043e375054a4f318c66342ee9ad31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc8a59662338ae99506795bdf8f3e570&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bea54a7e2da99c4d21fe120e09b5930&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-407b20f30b0250ff3bfa0029af7e723c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c748c9a23ba05cffbc5245984ffc52e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64bdf9c0794ec35908d392faea0893a5</data>
