  <data key="d0">Lithuania</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Lithuania is a country connected to Poland via the Suwalki Gap.&lt;SEP&gt;Lithuania is a country from which drones either fly over or launch from its territory to attack Russia, and Russia has officially declared Lithuania a participant in the conflict.&lt;SEP&gt;Lithuania is a country whose approach to the Russian threat and support for Ukraine is rooted in historical memory of Soviet occupation and repression.&lt;SEP&gt;Lithuania is a country whose former foreign minister confirmed Hungary's leaks.&lt;SEP&gt;Lithuania is a country that refused to allow Robert Fico's plane to fly over its territory.&lt;SEP&gt;Lithuania is one of the Baltic states whose ministers informed Robert Fico's office that they would not allow his plane through their airspace.</data>
