<node id="Soviet Union">
  <data key="d0">Soviet Union</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">The Soviet Union is the historical entity that occupied and repressed Lithuania, forming the basis of its historical memory.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union was a former communist state whose troops Viktor Orban demanded withdraw from Hungary in 1989.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union was the country whose troops were the target of the "Russians go home" slogan during the 1956 Hungarian Uprising.&lt;SEP&gt;Soviet Union was a country that collapsed, leading to the rise of Ukrainian and Russian criminal groups.&lt;SEP&gt;Soviet Union was the country whose forces suppressed the 1956 Hungarian Uprising, using tanks and violence.&lt;SEP&gt;Soviet Union is the historical state that suppressed the 1956 Hungarian uprising.&lt;SEP&gt;Soviet Union is the historical country that Viktor Orban says he opposed in his youth.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f1a89cef022ba72f7cec7e5ae7c29101&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30533205f101cc1df47f96e15592f2b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81536517f133c3a5924be660cac3eb05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b107034176b638d6ed0508c3346f0725&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5ab60c301522fe44f5b6ce532a3c05b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c8eeb9a8a3df6bc82ea6fb1da68ab0e</data>
