<node id="Robert Fico">
  <data key="d0">Robert Fico</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Robert Fico is a prominent Slovak politician who has served as the Prime Minister of Slovakia. His tenure has been marked by significant political challenges, including facing a no-confidence vote, a treason investigation, and accusations of abuse of power. He has also been accused of preparing for elections by accelerating changes to electoral legislation in an alleged attempt to manipulate the process. Fico has been linked to the actions of Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán, who is perceived to have acted in ways intended to help Fico win parliamentary elections; consequently, Fico is sometimes described as a "mini-Orban."

In the realm of foreign policy, Fico has taken several notable and often contradictory stances. He declared that Slovakia would not support the 20th European Union sanctions package against Russia and has opposed the transfer of frozen Russian assets to Ukraine. Fico has advocated for the restoration of the Druzhba pipeline to protect Slovak and Hungarian energy interests. He claimed that Slovakia became defenseless after donating MiG-29 fighter jets to Ukraine and did not condemn Russia for its strike on the Brody Oil Depot. Maintaining a pro-Russian stance, Fico seeks an alternative route to Moscow and plans to visit the Russian capital on May 9, though he faces obstacles from Baltic and Polish states. Despite these positions, Fico has also expressed support for Ukraine's EU accession, conducted negotiations with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy, and stated that a peace agreement with Russia is impossible without Ukraine's consent. Overall, his approach regarding Ukraine is seen as sharing the perspective of the Hungarian government.&lt;SEP&gt;Robert Fico is a politician from Slovakia who, along with Viktor Orban, is expected to unblock €90 billion for Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Robert Fico is a left-wing socialist politician who did not have a solo majority in parliament and formed a coalition with ultraright, anti-Ukraine forces.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11b9d96fc698fa7b9242168a7bad3295&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d2e8519cd0bab60a3e52b70a90d3f0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7fe37316c34f12bcbc2eaa45277e7b90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0db27d1e5bd672959a82744488e5a07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204b60f8b5f56bb209e8ca6cc9af48f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43d54b3b9775efd5f7d0080cad36c2de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09de750ab096b64385f95a95c7d0e5ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cab9a94ea286a7616cc63009e8c3d5ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-313fbd5b1968d3d281c042524d458b06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac57a8e21b0821ebfc4b7007fb6688a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116374b92e94e5c9f902ad74ec9408ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b80d70d8670ebee7e64e3613a75c65de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9d4541f93fbe1abbecc6f52128db7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b86c9560ec7e43e68be30c2e38dbbde</data>
