<node id="Peter Magyar">
  <data key="d0">Peter Magyar</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Péter Magyar is a Hungarian political figure, lawyer, and prominent opponent of Prime Minister Viktor Orbán. Originally an insider within the Orbán system and the former husband of Judit Varga, he has leveraged his inside knowledge to become a vocal critic of the government, exposing corruption. Magyar is the leader of the opposition Tisza Party (TISZA) and is positioned as a main rival to Orbán in upcoming elections, enjoying stable public support. He is pro-European, supports EU policy on Ukraine, and is willing to diversify energy supplies. He has stated he is open to negotiations with Russia if conditions allow, without becoming friends, and has used the issue of warming ties with Russia against Orbán, demanding the expulsion of Russian spies.

Magyar has been involved in several high-profile political actions and accusations. He has accused Viktor Orbán of using taxpayer funds to finance CPAC and of secretly helping Robert Fico through a migrant influx. He has also responded to accusations of planning violent actions, made statements about document destruction, and, in an interview on state television M1, announced the liquidation of the channel. Additionally, Magyar has reported on financial transfers and made public appeals. He has been the subject of a bot campaign in Hungary, with the text criticizing him. In other political contexts, Magyar calls on other opposition groups to withdraw from the elections to form a united front against the government, and his supporters have participated in mass rallies against Orbán's policies.

Magyar is portrayed by Orbán's propaganda as a puppet of foreign forces, and his name and initials have been duplicated by a registered "independent candidate" as a spoiler tactic. He has made a statement about winning a victory visible from the Kremlin. Overall, Magyar is a central opposition figure leading the Tisza Party, facing both direct political rivalry and demonization campaigns from the Orbán government.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar is a political figure in Hungary whose online speech viewership is compared to that of Viktor Orban.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar is an anti-corruption reformer who is currently leading in polls against Viktor Orban.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a865b7c03998478f1296272dd37b2e83&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1d17587159dea209c75a0ae5875a4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3da3b046ca1fff9119eaf735e34f56d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce845ea082895ffef253ac499ba46794&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b58528cbdfa8a329180c462cc03756dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4219648b35dcbd430c607633467c92dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde106bd95ba19880a7e7ad13fdc019d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cab9a94ea286a7616cc63009e8c3d5ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad59dda33fb37c7a475f7200ea184cf8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2886b7cb500c955cf1d8671ed22bd946&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3ef991a8152469dff039e1e39a042bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3311af1794addd390d80bf21ccd47d8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443c22f60ed93ec379e718efa356a140&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00452022e84a0076582b1330b967245d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c604c4b50688beffa97c1aa0f1b779&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f</data>
