<node id="Fidesz">
  <data key="d0">Fidesz</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Fidesz is a Hungarian political party that currently serves as the ruling party in the country, led by Viktor Orbán. Originally founded as a liberal movement, the party underwent a significant ideological shift to national-conservatism in 1994. Fidesz has held power for 16 years, during which it has established deep entrenchment of its loyalists within Hungarian state institutions. The party controls approximately 90% of the media and has used aggressive propaganda tactics, including official channels publishing generated videos, such as one about a girl waiting for her father to return from war. Fidesz has used its parliamentary supermajority to redraw electoral boundaries since 2012 and maintains control over the government and electoral system.

The party has faced numerous controversies and accusations, including allegations of orchestrating vote-buying campaigns, using intimidation tactics, and distributing bags to voters at some polling stations. During protests, Fidesz has been referred to by opponents as "Dirty Fidesz." Notably, Peter Magyar, a figure who later became prominent in opposition to the party, was once part of its nomenclature. Despite its long-standing dominance, Fidesz has recently experienced a shift in political fortunes, trailing in polls for the first time in 16 years and facing declining support ahead of elections. The party is now trailing behind the Tisza Party in polls. High voter turnout has been described as not very good news for the party and its leader. Fidesz has turned the 2026 parliamentary elections into a referendum on peace versus war, and the party's deputy submitted the relevant bill.&lt;SEP&gt;Fidesz is the ruling political party in Hungary led by Viktor Orban, traditionally strong in rural areas but experiencing panic and fear.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26fcbf6510a404d136a66a46e0584357&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30533205f101cc1df47f96e15592f2b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81536517f133c3a5924be660cac3eb05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3da3b046ca1fff9119eaf735e34f56d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-867b81690ecba5bc75830acd44c39131&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1561937403235278917e112e7843f5b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bae0e37e11b33519772a72128c43c6ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f70e0895097bbb48ff32f2b973c6e11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05e8d26fde09e1462e6b55210ee0396a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2886b7cb500c955cf1d8671ed22bd946&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeeb3e654a660cb7b38dfc9d61222bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769ff8feb3b00c3c503fb9e86e9bdf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c99964a997545fd96cbae2fac33e426b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f</data>
