<node id="Peter Szijjarto">
  <data key="d0">Peter Szijjarto</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Peter Szijjarto is the Hungarian Minister of Foreign Affairs. In this role, he has been characterized by a notably close and cooperative relationship with Russia, which has manifested in several specific actions and accusations. Szijjarto confirmed passing information about closed European Union meetings to Russian officials, and he has been described as acting on the instructions of Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov. He shared EU documents directly with Lavrov and maintained a direct hotline with him. Furthermore, Szijjarto cooperated with Russia to block EU sanctions, fought against a specific sanctions package, and made attempts to remove Russian companies from the EU sanctions list. He also complained about the EU hiding documents related to sanctions on an entity referred to as “2Rivers” and explained a delay in a vote as being due to Hungary and Slovakia. Beyond these political and diplomatic maneuvers, Szijjarto also signed a 12-point plan with the Russian Minister of Health, indicating a broader scope of bilateral cooperation. His actions have led to descriptions of him as effectively working for Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Szijjarto is the Minister of Foreign Affairs of Hungary who spoke with his Iranian counterpart.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Szijjarto is Hungary's foreign minister who was involved in leaked negotiations with Russian officials.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Szijjarto is a Hungarian official whose conversations with Sergey Lavrov have been leaked.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Szijjarto is the Hungarian Minister of Foreign Affairs who was criticized for failing to summon the Russian ambassador after a missile attack on Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Szijjarto is the Hungarian Foreign Minister who regularly calls Sergey Lavrov during EU meetings.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e1c1527de328b9a19ce7197568a1196b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde507aa2566c6c22d3e526f2ec971df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b346b60f2318d240edb84608cb2b374&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6610955fc2b94d091c65e9f7449d2028&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1d17587159dea209c75a0ae5875a4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d35dd378774e42749ede8cf940deb5eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c69b4fdab693c5bb396f844f3d8a77c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f7b78146485b6ecfc5184d01e665fc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-325a7fb30b39d268db124a71f1e8acc7</data>
