<node id="Tisza Party">
  <data key="d0">Tisza Party</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Tisza Party is a Hungarian political party currently led by Péter Magyar. It serves as the main opposition party in Hungary and has been leading in opinion polls against the ruling Fidesz party, with some surveys indicating support at approximately 49%. The party has reportedly won a constitutional majority in recent elections. The Tisza Party has been the subject of significant activity and controversy: its IT specialists were reportedly targeted for recruitment by Hungarian special services. Additionally, the party has faced claims of being financed by Ukraine, though such assertions remain a point of contention. The party has also held public rallies, including one in Budapest attended by Zsolt Hegedűs, further demonstrating its active political engagement within the country.&lt;SEP&gt;The Tisza Party is the main opposition party in Hungary led by Peter Magyar, advocating for a restrained position on aid to Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Tisza Party is a political party in Hungary that held a gathering in support of Peter Magyar.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e1c1527de328b9a19ce7197568a1196b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63ebd542c6a2099ce773883107cf0bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b58528cbdfa8a329180c462cc03756dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf472d3981c26e07231b309328f0597b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2886b7cb500c955cf1d8671ed22bd946&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00452022e84a0076582b1330b967245d</data>
