  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Kyiv">
  <data key="d0">Kyiv</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Kyiv is the capital city of Ukraine, serving as the country's primary seat of government and decision-making. As a central political entity, Kyiv is frequently referenced in the context of international relations, particularly concerning its interactions with Hungary. The city and its government have been the subject of accusations, such as being accused of interfering in Hungarian elections. In diplomatic and conflict-related matters, Kyiv is noted as the destination for several key interactions: Hungarian experts were sent there to negotiate regarding an oil blockade, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy invited Hungarian Prime Minister Robert Fico for a visit, and it was the intended destination of an Oschadbank cash transfer. The city's government is described as actively thinking and acting in relation to Hungary, situating Kyiv at the center of a political conflict with that nation. Additionally, the name "Kyiv" is used in a personal context, referring to a location an individual named Igor was given the option to travel to when stopped at the Hungarian border. The city also holds significance in the broader geopolitical landscape, notably regarding European support for Ukraine, which is described as being sabotaged by Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán.&lt;SEP&gt;Kyiv is the government of Ukraine that demands Brussels stop Russian energy imports.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-30533205f101cc1df47f96e15592f2b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ed5a8ece2f6bc4017c8fae3014bc239&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac57a8e21b0821ebfc4b7007fb6688a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf472d3981c26e07231b309328f0597b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1d344e42d77e1e71d20f49e3f03482d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-febe32c9e0da364a16a64ecb34a3ae7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3dc55aad4eb94544269bbfd9dec2905&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f26cc7528a3ccfcc5b72d2752bd95332</data>
