<node id="Budapest">
  <data key="d0">Budapest</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Budapest is the capital city of Hungary. Historically, Budapest was invaded twice in the 20th century and experienced a period of significant violence during the 1990s, when criminal groups operated within the city. During that era, a major explosion occurred in the city center near a McDonald's restaurant, with the central square identified as the precise location. In modern political contexts, Budapest has been characterized as an opposition stronghold; in the 2022 election, 17 out of 18 districts voted for the opposition, and the city recorded the highest voter turnout in Hungary. It has also been the site of large Fidesz advertising billboards, a march supporting Magyar, a Tisza Party rally, and a mass protest against Viktor Orbán.

In international affairs, Budapest was referenced as the entity that would be stripped of its veto power by a European Union plan. The city has been proposed by Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán as a potential venue for a peace summit between the United States and Russia and was a planned location for a meeting between Donald Trump and Vladimir Putin. Budapest has also been noted as the location of Marco Rubio's visit and as a place where J.D. Vance was located to support Orbán. The city is mentioned in the context of published correspondence with Moscow that confirms Russian influence, and it is where the Russian embassy hosts a GRU unit. A Russian special team reportedly arrived in Budapest, and Russian intelligence officers have also been noted as arriving there.

Budapest has been involved in various contentious activities. It is the headquarters of Semen Mogilevich's operations and the location where Dietmar Clodo was a key agent. The city is also the location in Hungary where Ukrainian citizens were allegedly mistreated while detained. Furthermore, Budapest has been referred to as the actor in the seizure of Ukrainian funds, and it is where detained Oschadbank vehicles are currently located, near a Hungarian security structure.&lt;SEP&gt;Budapest is the capital city of Hungary, used in the text as a metonym for the Hungarian government involved in EU discussions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6610955fc2b94d091c65e9f7449d2028&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec12d27878bbf1f79c741b043b995fd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b107034176b638d6ed0508c3346f0725&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c338d5794d84977817897ee6bca1756e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53047d8273819f991ab1b18d7532d438&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b163da87b444be6123192ff3f1b16be3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-372f1bcd0cd64c08c95815f34e60f974&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac226d815cf8e5ee5f29617fff9c6877&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ab176e3cbddf97c2d5cd15191ff861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1d17587159dea209c75a0ae5875a4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-363738684ef116828bdbb6070ee37a0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3da3b046ca1fff9119eaf735e34f56d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-867b81690ecba5bc75830acd44c39131&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1561937403235278917e112e7843f5b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35ef5418fbb73e10428a076cc8117782&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ccdb895c49cc5a1b4f5807c901e88cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63ebd542c6a2099ce773883107cf0bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1d38d0ea892917e129f8c929d603be9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04a007153cdf32c13e7e322795fc37d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec746b6d0ff03701a4a50f1703d6bbdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb3aa1bf6b71f9fbb7a7b41972196c5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21313de66f58c55ed37fed59c551bfe8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3ef991a8152469dff039e1e39a042bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cef394908f978f54c9d7b18dd4c332a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443c22f60ed93ec379e718efa356a140&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f94b6692f9007427868d3a0f71d9e5f</data>
