<node id="Péter Magyar">
  <data key="d0">Péter Magyar</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Péter Magyar is a Hungarian politician and the leader of the opposition Tisza Party, which is contesting the Hungarian parliamentary elections. He is widely regarded as the leader of the strongest opposition party and has been described as the future Prime Minister of Hungary. Magyar has promised that if he wins the election, the State Audit Office would investigate the assets of government members and representatives for the last 20 years. He has also been noted for giving a speech congratulating Russian propagandists in Hungary and for demanding that the European Union sever ties with Ukraine.

Magyar has stated that he was a victim of blackmail involving a secretly recorded intimate video, which he described as classic Russian-style kompromat. He has been targeted by disinformation campaigns portraying him as a Brussels puppet without external support. These descriptions present a figure who is both a leading opposition voice in Hungary and a subject of controversy and smear campaigns, with his political actions and statements drawing attention both domestically and in the context of European and Russian relations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fbfb4c02584693e7cef85affc74bcab8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bae0e37e11b33519772a72128c43c6ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81e671facba3c370c9128965308146dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-713408326a31f030b9c00f6efef043ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeeb3e654a660cb7b38dfc9d61222bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3960e17c128f750dfd948945c91a00ff</data>
