<node id="Tisza">
  <data key="d0">Tisza</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Tisza is a political party or movement in Hungary that functions as the primary opposition to the ruling Fidesz party. It is led by Péter Magyar (sometimes spelled Peter Magyar) and is presented as an alternative to Fidesz in national party list voting. The party is described as an opposition political force that leads in independent, centrist, and liberal opinion polls ahead of Hungarian parliamentary elections. In the context of political rivalries, Tisza has been mentioned in relation to vote-buying allegations against Fidesz.

The party has also been the subject of various accusations and external narratives. Authorities have accused Tisza of planning to provoke a civil war. Additionally, Russian strategy reportedly seeks to portray Tisza as a "war party" supporting Ukraine, framing the party's stance within the broader geopolitical conflict. These conflicting descriptions highlight the contentious political environment surrounding Tisza, where it is positioned both as a democratic opposition alternative and as a target of accusations and strategic disinformation campaigns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-867b81690ecba5bc75830acd44c39131&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1561937403235278917e112e7843f5b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bae0e37e11b33519772a72128c43c6ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeeb3e654a660cb7b38dfc9d61222bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f</data>
