<node id="Kim Jong Un">
  <data key="d0">Kim Jong Un</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Kim Jong Un is the supreme leader of North Korea, a global power figure whose actions and policies, including those of his proxies, are described as a threat to the European Union. He is the nation's dictator and has been involved in inspecting parts of a future monument and museum dedicated to the memory of North Korean soldiers. His strategic goals for the country include the technological modernization of its armed forces, with a specific focus on mastering drone technologies and tactics. In the context of international conflict, Kim Jong Un congratulated North Korean soldiers deployed to Russia to fight in the war against Ukraine and stated that major geopolitical changes are expected in the coming year. His regime supplies soldiers to Russia in exchange for support from Russian President Vladimir Putin. In matters of domestic succession and military leadership, Kim Jong Un has appointed his daughter to a leadership position in missile production as well as a position within North Korea's nuclear forces. Despite these appointments, his own power remains stable, and contrary to certain rumors, he does not take his daughter to water parks.&lt;SEP&gt;Kim Jong Un is the leader of North Korea who pursued strategic rapprochement with Vladimir Putin and signed a mutual military assistance treaty.&lt;SEP&gt;Kim Jong Un is a North Korean leader who ordered members of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party and Ministry of Defense officials to carry out landscaping tasks at the graves of North Korean soldiers killed in the war against Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;North Korean leader who was the subject of an insulting phrase used during a job interview to expose a hacker.&lt;SEP&gt;Kim Jong Un is the North Korean leader who expressed support for Russia's invasion of Ukraine and promised to help Moscow achieve victory.&lt;SEP&gt;Kim Jong Un is the leader of North Korea who called on youth to prepare for war in Ukraine on the side of Russia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1704b3bc09f596547c35a95941e29e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1769d39ef03a8083db256740e9cd0766&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec36c3f34e874fb6a0c44b533c707cfe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fce8f15f650ac7d354598ceb3c44ee55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8262c667cbee1913092248cf832b5b2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe4a537b10e5a1cd6b9731ae8a2ee0a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc8a59662338ae99506795bdf8f3e570&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b081d06450863ed7e420f49361e136e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f525f78f89f5b96d8fc7535b3303ae6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a32816fdb3610e6d8a54bb67883ce674&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef573f6547db918e0c04e9db6d87c22b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-407b20f30b0250ff3bfa0029af7e723c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-182d3ae7e14d1083d21cb4dce15639d9</data>
