<node id="South Korea">
  <data key="d0">South Korea</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">South Korea is a country to which the North Korean prisoners of war requested to be transferred.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is a country whose intelligence agency provided information about North Korean military supplies to Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is a country studied by Andrey Lankov, with its culture and mentality discussed in the interview.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is the country home to the Institute For Strategy Of National Security and the Bank Of Korea, and has a much larger economy than North Korea.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is a country whose intelligence agency, NIS, reported on the planned deployment of North Korean troops to Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is a country whose coast guard conducted a boarding operation described in the source text.</data>
