<edge source="European Union" target="Russia">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Russian military's combat experience from Ukraine is questioned for its applicability in a potential conflict with the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Union proposed the 20th sanctions package against Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;Russia is officially recognized by the European Union as a major security threat and seeks to undermine EU institutions.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Putin informed Viktor Orban that Russia's reaction to the EU decision on Russian assets would be strong.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Union maintains sanctions on Russian oil, as criticized by Orban.&lt;SEP&gt;Russia gained access to sensitive EU discussions through the Orban government, including physical access and cyber penetration.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Putin aims to influence the European Union by supporting populist parties to change political elites.</data>
  <data key="d9">access,conflict,espionage,influence,political strategy,potential conflict,retaliation,sanctions,security threat,undermining</data>
