<edge source="European Union" target="Ukraine">
  <data key="d7">11.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The European Union-Ukraine relationship is multifaceted, encompassing financial aid, political tensions regarding membership, and differing geopolitical perspectives. Financially, the European Union has been heavily involved in supporting Ukraine, with a significant focus on a substantial loan package of 90 billion euros. This amount is mentioned in multiple contexts, including a consideration for a war loan, a plan for budget deficit financing approved in December 2025, and a generally approved loan. However, this aid is at times politically contentious, as it has been reported that Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán has blocked some EU aid and sanctions directed at Ukraine. The question of Ukraine's membership in the European Union is a major point of contention. Viktor Orbán has publicly stated that Ukraine’s accession would mean the EU would effectively join Ukraine’s war. He has also accused Brussels and Kyiv of attempting to force Ukraine's membership. Furthermore, a separate viewpoint, attributed to Fidesz propaganda, blames the European Union for sending money to Ukraine. The overall relationship is thus defined by substantial planned and approved financial commitments from the EU to Ukraine, set against significant political obstacles and opposition, particularly from Hungary, concerning the terms of that aid and the broader strategic path of Ukrainian integration into the EU.&lt;SEP&gt;The demanded action was for the European Union to sever its ties with Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Ukraine's membership in the European Union is described by Orban as posing a risk of drawing the EU into war with Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Union finances the repair of the Ukrainian section of the Druzhba pipeline and provides technical support.</data>
  <data key="d9">accusation,aid,blame,break ties,budget support,conflict,financial allocation,financial assistance,financial support,financing,loan,membership,risk,sanctions,severance,technical support,war</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204b60f8b5f56bb209e8ca6cc9af48f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77680239477915203c692473a1450584&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfe8b96b31b63d5ed58e1db0f1170774&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b80d70d8670ebee7e64e3613a75c65de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-870499425ae897e4d4a7fe9c0c2b515c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1d344e42d77e1e71d20f49e3f03482d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-713408326a31f030b9c00f6efef043ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f26cc7528a3ccfcc5b72d2752bd95332&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9d4541f93fbe1abbecc6f52128db7e</data>
