<edge source="Hungary" target="Viktor Orban">
  <data key="d7">9.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Viktor Orban is the Prime Minister and leader of Hungary, actively leading the government ahead of events such as the April 12th elections. His political career is closely associated with the current regime in Hungary, where his government maintains control over state media and the election system. Orban has been quoted as the source of official statements, including decisions regarding Hungary's suspension of transit. He is credited with personally ensuring Hungary's energy security. However, his leadership is also characterized by a refusal to conduct anti-corruption reforms, instead maintaining a system of redistributing money through state tenders. Due to his political influence and governance style, the potential for his removal from European Union politics has been discussed, particularly in the context of the country's national elections.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orban serves as the Prime Minister of Hungary and represents the country's position on the oil blockade.</data>
  <data key="d9">corruption,election,energy security,governance,government,influence,leadership,political association,representation,statement</data>
