<edge source="Viktor Orban" target="Peter Magyar">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Peter Magyar demanded Orban expel Russian spies, drawing a historical parallel to the 1956 uprising.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orban is the main political rival of Peter Magyar in the election.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar replaced Viktor Orban, who was a Kremlin puppet, with a pro-European policy stance.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orban's propaganda attacks Peter Magyar as a puppet of foreign forces to discredit the opposition.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar criticizes Viktor Orban's concentration of power and policies.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar called Viktor Orban a "traitor" following reports of Moscow's planned information campaign.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar's speeches had significantly more viewers than Viktor Orban's speeches.</data>
  <data key="d9">accusation,comparison,competition,conflict,contrast,criticism,demand,hostility,opposition,political opposition,politics,rivalry,successor,viewership</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-3da3b046ca1fff9119eaf735e34f56d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443c22f60ed93ec379e718efa356a140&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00452022e84a0076582b1330b967245d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c604c4b50688beffa97c1aa0f1b779</data>
